                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/174: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-09T20:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1919, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3074. For <persName corresp="#p_PFL">Polk</persName>; also <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName>. President has approved charter of
                    45,000 tons of shipping to Russian Embassy here for transporting supplies from
                    British and French ports to forces of <persName corresp="#p_YGNN1">General
                        Yudenitch</persName>. Embassy now negotiating with Shipping Board.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
